        "subject": "LU-00000 lustre: split non-Linux functions from linux-wait.h",
        "message": "LU-00000 lustre: split non-Linux functions from linux-wait.h\n\nlinux-wait.h in libcfs contains some wait macros that duplicate\nfunctionality in (recent) Linux, and also some macros that add new\nfunctionality.\n\nSplit the new macros out into a new lustre_wait.h (they are only using\nin lustre, not lnet).  This makes it easier to strip compatability\ncode when transforming lustre for upstream submission.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mr NeilBrown <neilb@suse.de>\nChange-Id: I02bda237b351c097bc251064567331c02540440b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
